00:00:55.780 --> 00:01:01.479
Leoben Minimum Security Prison in Austria
looks more like a high-end apartment complex

00:01:01.479 --> 00:01:07.310
than a prison. It has an abundant amount of
natural light, a court-yard, and barred off

00:01:07.310 --> 00:01:12.520
balconies. And, the average prisoner gets
their own kitchenette, comfortable furniture,

00:01:12.520 --> 00:01:18.770
and a TV. Inmates can also enjoy a game of
tennis, indoor soccer, a weight room, or romantic

00:01:18.770 --> 00:01:21.010
conjugal visit suites.

00:01:21.010 --> 00:01:26.340
At the other end of the prison spectrum is
the US Penitentiary, Administrative Maximum

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:32.410
Facility, or ADX, located in Florence, Co.
It was constructed in response to several

00:01:32.410 --> 00:01:38.560
security breaches and correctional officer
injuries at other maximum security prisons.

00:01:38.560 --> 00:01:43.950
ADX is best known for housing inmates who
have been deemed too dangerous, too high-profile,

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:49.260
or too great a national security risk such
as leaders of violent gangs, domestic and

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:55.530
foreign terrorists, and inmates at high escape-risk.
Cells have a desk, a stool, and a bed which

00:01:55.530 --> 00:02:00.770
are almost entirely made out of concrete,
as well as a toilet that shuts itself off

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:05.170
