Alcatraz is one of the most well known prisons
in the world. It was a maximum high security

00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:16.249
federal prison located on Alcatraz Island
in the San Francisco bay, and operated from

00:02:16.249 --> 00:02:23.249
1934-1963. It was designed to hold prisoners
who continually caused trouble at other federal

00:02:23.569 --> 00:02:28.269
prisons, and held some of the most hardened
criminals in Americas history including Al

00:02:28.269 --> 00:02:33.670
Capone and George "Machine Gun" Kelly. It
was believed to be inescapable and America's

00:02:33.670 --> 00:02:40.060
strongest prison. A total of 36 prisoners
made 14 escape attempts during its 29 years

00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:47.060
of operation, but it was closed march 21st,
1963 due to high maintenance costs and a poor

00:02:47.590 --> 00:02:48.590
reputation.

00:02:48.590 --> 00:02:54.590
Aranjuez Prison in Spain is the only one in
the world to house two-parent inmate families.

00:02:54.590 --> 00:03:00.200
The units come with cribs, Disney characters
on the walls, and have access to a playground.

00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:04.879
When the children turn 3 they have to leave
the prison to be looked after by family. They're

00:03:04.879 --> 00:03:09.169
still debating on the success of the program
and the health of the children, so there are

00:03:09.169 --> 00:03:11.200
no plans to expand the program.

